      "message": "This doesn\u0027t cover actual Update working correctly with puts \u0026 deletes, which is more important.\n\nWDYT about merging this with above test by evolving existing config:\n\n  1. Re-enable the project by updating fallback group name to no longer be fallback.\n    This also adds coverage for matching 2 groups, which I think is missing right now.\n  2. Add new host/repo to the main group and delete ex-fallback group.\n    This adds both deletes \u0026 puts in an update, and also tests multiple hosts.\n\nunrelated to listUpdates, i think we need coverage for \u003e1 LUCI project, maybe\n\n  3. Add new LUCI project watching the previously deleted fallback group.\n\n\nThe upside of the proposed test is that iff we decide later to change implementation to, say, entirely in Redis, we\u0027d only need to change initial setup, not what is being asserted.",
